parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the automatic high beam system can cause the high beams to remain on when approaching oncoming traffic, blinding them and potentially leading to accidents or road rage incidents.
symptoms: The high beams turn on and off constantly
fail to dim for oncoming traffic
remain on when approaching oncoming traffic
fail to reactivate after passing by a vehicle with its headlights on
and are erratic in their operation.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A malfunctioning wireless cell phone charger can cause distraction while driving, leading to potential accidents.
symptoms: The wireless charger light blinks
the phone never charges
the charger starts and stops charging
the phone gets hot
the charger does not work with different phones or cases.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the idle-stop system can cause the vehicle to fail to restart, leading to potential accidents or strandings.
symptoms: The vehicle fails to restart after idle-stop engagement
multiple attempts to restart are required
dash indicators are lit.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The activation of multiple safety warning lights can cause driver distraction, leading to potential accidents.
symptoms: Multiple safety warning lights activate on the dashboard
the vehicle does not accelerate normally
the brake warning light activates without any obstacles.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An engine fire can cause serious damage to the vehicle and potential harm to occupants.
symptoms: Warning lights activate
the vehicle shuts down
smoke comes from the engine
flames erupt from the hood.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A malfunctioning auto highbeam lighting system can cause glare and confusion for oncoming drivers, leading to potential accidents.
symptoms: The auto highbeam lighting continuously flashes when seeing reflections from street signs.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Power Loss and Check Engine Light Flashing
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden loss of engine power and flashing check engine light can cause a hazardous situation, especially when driving on the interstate, as it can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The check engine light begins flashing
the vehicle experiences a significant loss of power
the engine shakes
the vehicle is unable to accelerate
the tachometer goes to zero
and the econ mode is enabled.
